Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange Kuroki. Age: 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.25,0:02:13.72,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"AHSMB's Shadow"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.17,0:02:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently this is a real problem child.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.55,0:02:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a pilot, Ange is highly skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.84,0:02:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange is taking full advantage \Nof the unit's capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.72,0:02:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are considerable
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.34,0:02:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,problems on the cooperation \Nand social skills end.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.08,0:02:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to see a bit \Nmore mental stability!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.64,0:02:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That very issue has the \Nother five members
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.05,0:02:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of Team Rabbits terrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.10,0:02:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good thing Izuru is the leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.97,0:02:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone else, and I imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.77,0:02:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the team would be in even worse shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.44,0:02:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we're forcing \Nanother toughie on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.79,0:02:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.54,0:02:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Officer Ange?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.86,0:02:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.05,0:02:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-sorry! I didn't mean to startle you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.21,0:03:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-no, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.93,0:03:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tend to get lost in my own \Nworld when I'm concentrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.07,0:03:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.74,0:03:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were like that on the \Nbattlefield yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.23,0:03:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.43,0:03:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said a bunch of rude \Nthings back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.77,0:03:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, hey! Don't worry about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.57,0:03:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.78,0:03:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Officer Ange?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.61,0:03:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please quit calling me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.45,0:03:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm younger than you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.44,0:03:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, th-then how about Officer Kuroki?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.13,0:03:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not that either...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.95,0:03:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about Angie?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.40,0:03:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you ever call me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.16,0:03:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what should I call you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By my name without any titles...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.46,0:03:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-you won't get upset?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.93,0:03:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.60,0:03:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.35,0:03:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Ange.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.23,0:03:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.11,0:03:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, how may I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.07,0:04:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was I doing here...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.57,0:04:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No point in asking me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.32,0:04:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, now I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.32,0:04:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to invite you to train with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.95,0:04:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have morning training!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.33,0:04:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Training?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.39,0:04:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to train with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.15,0:04:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I guess you don't want to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even at school, I always \Ntrained by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're handling Black \N6's maintenance alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.92,0:04:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. It's less stressful this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.51,0:04:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus it helps me memorize \Nthe unit's frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.09,0:04:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we're a team, so we really \Nshould train together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will if it's an order!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.77,0:04:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I've been meaning to \Nask you, Officer Ange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.44,0:04:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, um, are you a guy or a-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.82,0:04:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to get changed, \Nso please go on ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.66,0:04:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you never asked if \NAnge is a guy or a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.24,0:04:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... It's hard to work \Nthat into the conversation...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.75,0:04:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid I'll accidentally step
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.23,0:04:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on a landmine and set \Nhim off like yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.71,0:04:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you been through something \Nlike that once before?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.84,0:05:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any good \Nideas or suggestions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.20,0:05:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.94,0:05:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't Ange a funny, vivacious girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.91,0:05:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm dying to become \Nfriends with her so I can
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.70,0:05:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,go to her room and have sleepovers!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.91,0:05:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only if Ange is a girl, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.44,0:05:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you call her a \N"hot guy" just yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.30,0:05:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.10,0:05:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I was thinking, why \Ndon't we show him
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.80,0:05:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that video Randy gave us a while back?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.85,0:05:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.17,0:05:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We could figure out Ange's \Ngender based on his reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.83,0:05:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! I think it's pretty normal
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.14,0:05:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for guys our age to \Nbe interested in sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.58,0:05:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you say that \Nwith a straight face?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.25,0:05:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're going through with this,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.76,0:05:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,let's borrow something more inten-
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.88,0:05:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scum balls!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.42,0:05:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot how good her hearing was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.05,0:05:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.84,0:05:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean to take so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.60,0:05:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.79,0:05:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't tell if Ange \Nis a guy or a girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.22,0:05:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this is our chance \Nto show off and shine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.72,0:06:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter? We've only run 10km.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.86,0:06:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we've got 3G pressing down on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are your heart and \Nlungs made out of?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.50,0:06:21.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Ange!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.63,0:06:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi is really good at this, \Nso don't let your guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.02,0:06:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.73,0:06:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Ready, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.93,0:06:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First I need to set up my formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.06,0:06:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Game over!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.31,0:06:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange wins!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.29,0:06:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.83,0:06:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She actually beat Asagi in a simulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.42,0:06:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She concentrated her fire, broke \Nthrough his central forces,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.80,0:06:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,attacked from behind and annihilated \Nthe surrounding forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.20,0:06:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The speed of the maneuver \Ndetermined its success.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.74,0:06:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! I got caught in \Nthe heat of the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.39,0:06:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accidentally went all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.52,0:07:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, ow, ow, ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.29,0:07:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my current baby!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.57,0:07:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Scissorhands 16401,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.30,0:07:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a prototype made by the \NGDF's Development Team!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.07,0:07:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They equipped it with a totally new \Nenergy unit type that has beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.83,0:07:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,mechanical functionality that \Nprioritizes practicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.68,0:07:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, that gave \Nit a fresh new design!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.14,0:07:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it applies the same idea \Nbehind how the AHSMB work!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.29,0:07:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like my Gold 4, you can attach
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.81,0:07:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a bunch of stuff to this \Nhottie's core block.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.18,0:07:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, you can use it as a sniper \Nrifle or as an assault rifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.86,0:07:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It also functions as a missile \Nlauncher, a laser gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.52,0:07:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a taser grenade launcher, a phonon \Nmaser and a high-performance air rifle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.10,0:07:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It kills me when I think
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.36,0:07:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about how I coulda shined \Nif I had this puppy with me
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.70,0:07:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when we infiltrated that enemy ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.04,0:07:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally-
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.12,0:07:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't take very good care of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.58,0:07:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, it has a nice design,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.82,0:07:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but its performance as a \Nmulti-purpose rifle still
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.54,0:07:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha-?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.17,0:07:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it can be applied to anything, \Neach gun is only B-rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.92,0:07:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In space, a phonon maser \Nhas no practical use.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.32,0:07:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And switching scopes from gun \Nto gun is hardly acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.56,0:07:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that military \Ntechnology tends to fall for
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.92,0:08:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the lure of making weapons either \Ntoo massive or too versatile.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think this falls under that category.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.69,0:08:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, my Black 6 is \Na new generation of AHSMB
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.32,0:08:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,made by focusing on the unit's \Nheavy armor and armament.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.52,0:08:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I believe that this era \Ncalls for pursuing simplified,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.45,0:08:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,specialized weapons and arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.16,0:08:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.43,0:08:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know more about weapons than Suruga!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.84,0:08:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, this is simply what \Nwe learned in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.38,0:08:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you attend Instructor \NSuzukaze's classes as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.09,0:08:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-skill beats rote memory \Nany day of the week!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.06,0:08:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-my stomach...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.99,0:08:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.07,0:08:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have snacks after \Nour training sessions!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.24,0:08:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I've heard that Officer Ange \Nwas also good at Home Ec.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.58,0:09:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So when I asked him to make something,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.05,0:09:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kei decided to pitch in...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.73,0:09:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shoulda stopped her!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you mumbling about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It tastes best when \Nit's fresh, so eat up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.88,0:09:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this three times \Nmore potent than usual?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.81,0:09:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it just a blob of sugar?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mine's ready, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.89,0:09:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.44,0:09:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has a refined taste!\N And it's soft on the tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.04,0:09:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And best yet, it's not too sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.49,0:09:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't sweet at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.67,0:09:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, you're the only human \Nout there who feels that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.17,0:09:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.21,0:09:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Teoria?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.84,0:09:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.31,0:10:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am allowed to walk \Nabout more freely now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.51,0:10:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that the GDF's \Nofficials have realized that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.80,0:10:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have allied myself with \Nthe people of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.90,0:10:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I am not \Nallowed to speak with
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.61,0:10:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just anyone as of yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.73,0:10:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they said that I may hold brief
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.42,0:10:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,private conversations with \Nthose aware of the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.99,0:10:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're the first \Nperson I wanted to see!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.46,0:10:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-you came to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.58,0:10:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.53,0:10:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the way out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.00,0:10:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are my friend, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.26,0:10:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-but I don't remember \Nanything about you, Teoria!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.10,0:10:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of my old memories have been erased
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.23,0:10:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'm not allowed to \Nrevive those memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.81,0:10:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then please tell me \Nabout your current life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.78,0:10:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the team leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.11,0:10:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.45,0:11:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to everyone's help and \Nsupport, I'm managing somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.35,0:11:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm a truly horrible leader...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.20,0:11:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth is losing the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.15,0:11:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I can barely handle \Nthe missions I'm on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.92,0:11:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't control my \NAHSMB unit worth squat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.21,0:11:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And who knows when that Jiart \Nguy is going to show up again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.14,0:11:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Asagi and Kei \Nmust feel apprehensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.86,0:11:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They just keep it to themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.86,0:11:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I can't do a darn thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.35,0:11:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be a hero and \Nprotect everyone, but...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.30,0:11:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.36,0:11:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know dumping all of \Nthis on you won't help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.24,0:11:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't changed, Izuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.36,0:11:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before your memories were erased,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.61,0:11:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you often told me the exact same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.37,0:11:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I want to become a hero."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.21,0:11:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.21,0:11:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was one other thing you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.13,0:11:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd say, "I will protect you, Teoria."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.84,0:12:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It made me so happy when you said that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.97,0:12:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, in my eyes, you were a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.36,0:12:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-you've just made me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.52,0:12:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you thought of me that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.40,0:12:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I want you to promise me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.99,0:12:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, no matter what happens, \Npromise you'll come back alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.95,0:12:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are my hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.92,0:12:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.80,0:12:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my emergency pager!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.81,0:12:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This mission is called \NOperation: Goliath.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.44,0:12:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than engage in battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.63,0:12:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you are to rescue a \Nsupply ship in distress.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.54,0:13:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The supply ship that Team Doberman \Nwas temporarily operating
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.59,0:13:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,got trapped in the irregular gravity \Nbelt, the Ship Grave Attracter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.17,0:13:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are currently unable to break free.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.13,0:13:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normal ships cannot get \Nclose enough to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.20,0:13:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Team Rabbits, you are to \Nrepair the supply ship
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.84,0:13:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and help them get out! That is all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.71,0:13:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a pretty peaceful mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.01,0:13:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't believe we're helping \Na ship in distress.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.29,0:13:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A mission is still a mission!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do our best to save \Nour senior officers!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.07,0:13:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so pumped up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.18,0:13:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All six units have blasted off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.31,0:13:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The path to their target is clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.87,0:13:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5's Harmonic Levels are high.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.62,0:13:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.03,0:13:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ship Grave Attracter is composed \Nof cascading gravitational rapids
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.47,0:13:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,created by the spatial distortions \Nmade by celestial bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.24,0:13:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the name implies, it \Nis a graveyard for ships
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.79,0:13:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that have gotten caught in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.57,0:13:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so look out for debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.58,0:13:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer Ange, how is Black 6 holding up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.67,0:13:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, everything looks good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.42,0:14:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like she hasn't snapped yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let your guard down!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.26,0:14:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows what will flip his switch?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.59,0:14:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're entering the \Nirregular gravity belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.40,0:14:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.71,0:14:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a waterslide!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.41,0:14:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting swept away!\N No, I'm falling! I can't tell!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.44,0:14:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Debris!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.71,0:14:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dodge around it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.77,0:14:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kick back an' go with the flow ?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.18,0:14:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is really stinkin' pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.17,0:14:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just had to suggest \Ntaking that shortcut!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.30,0:14:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.01,0:14:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And without our Rhinos, \Nour hands are tied!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.70,0:14:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You agreed with the idea 'cause \Nyou were eager to get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.85,0:14:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wonder who they'll \Nsend to help us...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.47,0:14:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is understaffed \Nthe way the GDF
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.13,0:14:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is reorganizing the fleets.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Team Rabbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.77,0:15:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.56,0:15:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're here to help!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.08,0:15:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They sent you guys?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.02,0:15:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Randy, guys, did any of you get hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.61,0:15:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.96,0:15:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we've got some debris caught \Nin the engine and can't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.37,0:15:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd love to give you a hand, \Nbut we can't go outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.91,0:15:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to clear \Nthe engine on your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.79,0:15:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first and third boosters \Nhave suffered minor damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.21,0:15:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we repair these two,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.59,0:15:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you should be able to muster the \Npropulsion needed to break free.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.13,0:15:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2, issue the repair orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.09,0:15:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black 6, watch the perimeter!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.01,0:15:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.00,0:15:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enemies approaching from above!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.15,0:15:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for you, Earthlings!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.88,0:15:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surprise enemy attack! \NMultiple incoming fighters!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.90,0:15:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the one that fought Red \N5 in the Battle of Ceres!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.53,0:15:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.51,0:15:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're only lightly armed \Nfor the rescue mission!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.32,0:15:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4 and Rose 3, continue \Nwith the repairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.66,0:15:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else, intercept the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.62,0:15:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.62,0:15:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, Tamaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.37,0:16:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Patrick?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.47,0:16:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.46,0:16:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that unit-?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.09,0:16:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is my only lamata!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.05,0:16:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do as you will with the weaklings!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.43,0:16:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black 6 is intercepting!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.09,0:16:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me a good time, my lamata!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.26,0:16:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm intercepting!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.73,0:16:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer Ange!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.52,0:16:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've done it, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.52,0:16:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He snapped!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.69,0:16:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take me lightly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.86,0:16:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back! He's only after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.12,0:16:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Outta my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.74,0:16:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't run from me, coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.22,0:16:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hit me from the front if you're a man!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.50,0:16:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black 6 can't keep up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.64,0:16:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black 6, fall back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.41,0:16:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't out-maneuver him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.10,0:16:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit flappin' yer damn traps!\N Leave me the hell alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.18,0:16:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are undeserving to be my lamata.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.76,0:16:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your genes are hardly worth harvesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.68,0:17:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.66,0:17:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I could get in my Rhinos, \NI could have gone to save him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.60,0:17:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't we offer fire \Nsupport or somethin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.94,0:17:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The turret's control unit is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.62,0:17:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't rotate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.42,0:17:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You hear that, bunnies?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.53,0:17:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry and finish the repairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.53,0:17:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give ya an earful later \Nif ya don't hop to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.28,0:17:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last one! Ready and here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.70,0:17:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice! Leave the rest to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.09,0:17:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider it an honor for \Nme to hunt you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.20,0:17:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.77,0:17:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.72,0:17:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.86,0:17:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5's Harmonic Levels suddenly spiked!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.22,0:17:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like when they \Nwent on their first sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.91,0:18:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, calm down! Pull back for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.50,0:18:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.48,0:18:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what I have been waiting for!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.93,0:18:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.41,0:18:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.89,0:18:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you put on a rather good show.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.48,0:18:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I want you to promise me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.52,0:18:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens, promise \Nyou'll come back alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.42,0:18:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5's frame just changed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.06,0:18:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.64,0:19:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.93,0:19:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that another new AHSMB?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.68,0:19:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5's Harmonic Level has \Nreached its former peak level.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.60,0:19:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...! I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.26,0:19:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.51,0:19:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you are not yet done \Nbringing me enjoyment!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.27,0:20:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You make my genes boil!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.76,0:21:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that really Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.68,0:21:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5's body can't keep \Nup with Izuru's commands!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.69,0:21:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.90,0:21:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too much for the unit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.61,0:21:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's already maximized \NRed 5's motor abilities!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.03,0:21:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.89,0:21:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There! The repairs are all done!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.63,0:21:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Tamaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.32,0:21:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Propulsion System: OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.87,0:21:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.54,0:21:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn to three o'clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.25,0:21:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Point the turret at the enemy fighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.54,0:21:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.43,0:21:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet another nuisance!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.98,0:21:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've run out of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this only serves \Nto whet my interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.52,0:22:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru! Are you okay, Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.15,0:22:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru! Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.61,0:22:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.04,0:23:56.02,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"Defending Vesta"
